summary: This is an FBI interview summary (302 form) from September 16, 2010, detailing an interview with a female individual regarding her encounter with Jeffrey Epstein. She describes being introduced to an opportunity for a paid massage, traveling to a Palm Beach residence, and identifying Epstein as the man who received the massage. The interview was conducted at the Palm Beach County Resident Agency.

persons.name: Jeffrey Epstein
persons.role: Subject of the interview, recipient of massage
persons.context: Identified from a photograph as the older man who received a massage from the interviewee at a Palm Beach residence. He paid her $200 after the encounter ended awkwardly when he attempted to touch her.

events.title: Massage encounter with Jeffrey Epstein
events.description: The interviewee traveled to a residence on Palm Beach to give a massage. She identified Jeffrey Epstein as the man who received the massage. During the massage, Epstein rolled onto his back and attempted to touch her, at which point she backed away and stated she had a boyfriend. Epstein paid her $200 and appeared angry.

events.title: FBI interview at Palm Beach County Resident Agency
events.description: The FBI interviewed an individual regarding her past encounter with Jeffrey Epstein. She provided details about being introduced to the opportunity, the location, and identifying Epstein from a photograph.

keyFacts: The interviewee was introduced to a paid massage opportunity by a friend of a friend (LNU) who was approximately 18-19 years old.
She traveled to a residence on Palm Beach where 3-4 other girls were present, and she identified Jeffrey Epstein from a photograph as the man who received the massage.
During the massage, Epstein attempted to touch her after rolling onto his back; she backed away, stated she had a boyfriend, and the massage ended.
Epstein paid her $200 in cash (two one-hundred dollar bills) and appeared angry about how the encounter concluded.
The document is an FBI 302 form, indicating this information was collected as part of a federal investigation.
